{
  "stem": "888.3",
  "chunk_idx": 13,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 69,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You know, because these other people who were in Hirschberg, you know, at that particular time-- which I found out later-- and their, their lot was really, really, you know-- traveling, you know, in these-- even in-- first of all, they marched them in these weathers where, at that particular time between February and March, there is rains, and sleet, and all kind of [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] you know, freezing.",
      "word_count": 71
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 70,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There was freezing weather.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 70,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "At night you used to freeze.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 70,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You know, you would freeze your bone.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 70,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You know?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 70,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And in the daytime, they, you know, were marching, you know?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 70,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then, of course, at certain spots they, they would take them and put them into these wagons.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 70,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Some people, they tried to-- this was already towards the end of the war, you know?",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 70,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I mean, the war was going on all around them.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 70,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Some, they were trying to take up to the mountains and, you know, get rid of them.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 70,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And lots of times, they were cut off.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 70,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "You know, the trains were cut off, so they had to take them back.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 70,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And they wound up in [?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 70,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Buchenwald. ?] So Martin, what were you most angry at the Germans about?",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 71,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, we were angry for the inhumanity-- the way they treated human beings, you know?",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 71,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I mean, first of all, you know, just going and uproot you from your place.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 71,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I mean, of course, figuring, what right do they have?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 71,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I mean, they are Germans.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 71,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They have their country.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 72,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I understand war, you understand?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 72,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "OK?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 72,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But I mean, this was a country which they were supposed to be allies.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 72,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You know, and they came in, you understand, they uprooted, and, and took your family, and then killed them for only being Jewish, you know?",
      "word_count": 25
    }
  ],
